markets.  Achieve monthly and quarterly channel revenue targets.  Organize forecast and pipeline weekly and monthly reviews with all assigned partners to attain forecast accuracy. Partner Recruitment &amp; Ecosystem ExpansionIdentify suitable prospect partners, sell the value of the NetSuite channel partner program, and recruit new channel partners based on the business needs, prioritizing high-growth and underserved markets. Build and maintain a partner landscape aligned with the regional GTM strategy.  Assess market coverage gaps and implement plans to expand presence across African regions. Business Planning &amp; Partner Development Collaborate with partners to build quarterly and yearly business plans focusing on driving NetSuite channel business and revenue acceleration.  Coordinate with partner enablement team on programs to drive partner competency based on regional maturity levels and partner capabilities.  Connect channel partners to internal supporting functions to enhance partners knowledge on value proposition of NetSuite. Relationship Management &amp; Advocacy Build trusted advisor relationships with partner executives and leadership teams.  Promote customer success stories and encourage partner-led references across the region.  Foster long-term, strategic engagement with partners to increase market penetration. Internal Collaboration Share best practices and collaborate with peer partner managers globally.  Represent African partner needs internally to influence Oracle‚Äôs SaaS strategy. Requirements &amp; Qualifications 5+ years in enterprise software sales, channel management, or alliances. Language skills: very good knowledge of written and spoken English, Zulu or Afrikaans skills.Current South Africa market knowledge for not less than 2 years of experienceExperience working with SaaS, ERP, CRM, or business applications.Ability to operate effectively in emerging and fast-growing markets.Strong communication, negotiation, and relationship-building 